ml.alternet.parser.handlers

Class TreeHandler<T,R extends T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ml.alternet.parser.handlers.TreeHandler<T,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the nodes in the target data structure.
    R - The type of the top node in the target data structure.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Supplier<R>, Rewindable, EventsHandler, Handler, DataHandler<R>, ValueMapper<T>, ValueStack.Stackable<ValueMapper.Value<T>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NodeBuilder, ValueBuilder

    public abstract class TreeHandler<T,R extends T>
extends Object
implements DataHandler<R>, ValueMapper<T>, ValueStack.Stackable<ValueMapper.Value<T>>
    A tree handler builds a target data structure while parsing with the help of a stack.
    Author:
    Philippe Poulard

      • mark

        public void mark()
        Description copied from interface: Rewindable
        Mark the present position.

        This method can be called safely several times.

        For each mark set, there should be sooner or later one consume or cancel.

      • consume

        public void consume()
             throws IllegalStateException
        Description copied from interface: Rewindable
        Consume the operations performed so far.

        This implies that the last marked position is removed and the next operation goes on from the current position. If there wasn't other marker, it will be impossible to go back. If there was at least another one marker, it can be itself cancelled or consumed independently.

        Specified by:
        consume in interface Rewindable
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - When this method is called whereas no position was marked so far.
        See Also:
        Rewindable.mark()
